Docker Knowledgebase

Docker File
------------------
This the text file which contain the commands which can be used to create the container image.
This will have the instruction which can be run on Commond line


Docker Image
------------------
Template to create a container

Docker Container
-----------------
Running instance of the docker image
It contains the package

Docker Commands
-----------------
-- docker -v or docker --version (for version)
-- docker pull [image_name]  (Pull image)
-- docker search [image_name] (Search image)
-- docker images (to show all the images)
-- docker run [image_name] (Run image)
-- docker ps -a (show all containers)
-- docker run -name [containerName] -d (for detach mode) [Image_Name]
-- docker run -name [containerName] -it (interactive mode) -d (for detach) [Image_Name]
-- docker exec  -it (interactive mode) [containder_Id] command
-- docker inspect [continer_id] (to get the details of the container)
-- docker stop [containerName] (to stop the container)
-- docker rm [containerName] (to remove the container)
-- docker rmi [imageName] (to remove the image)

Docker File
---------------
-- Create docker file
-- docker build -t [customimagename](must be lowercase) . (After name add space and dot)
